 more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ellen Fortis was born about 1130, in Chellington, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Simon Fortis , of Chellington, was 15 and her mother, Mrs Simon Fortis of Chellington, was 15. She had at least 1 son with Osmund Mordaunt , of Radwell."},"et":{"about 1130–":"umbes 1130–Surnud","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1130–1197":"1130–1197","1158–1231":"1158–1231","1117–Male":"1117–Surnud","1117–Female":"1117–Surnud","1117":"1117","1158":"1158","about 1158":"umbes 1158","1231":"1231","1197":"1197","1130":"1130","about 1130":"umbes 1130","Radwell, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chellington, Bedfordshire, England":"Chellington, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1130–":"noin 1130–Kuollut","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","1130–1197":"1130–1197","1158–1231":"1158–1231","1117–Male":"1117–Kuollut","1117–Female":"1117–Kuollut","1117":"1117","1158":"1158","about 1158":"noin 1158","1231":"1231","1197":"1197","1130":"1130","about 1130":"noin 1130","Radwell, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Chellington, Bedfordshire, England":"Chellington, Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1130–":"environ 1130–Décédée","1130–Female":"1130–Décédée","1130–1197":"1130–1197","1158–1231":"1158–1231","1117–Male":"1117–Décédé","1117–Female":"1117–Décédée","1117":"1117","1158":"1158","about 1158":"environ 1158","1231":"1231","1197":"1197","1130":"1130","about 1130":"environ 1130","Radwell, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Chellington, Bedfords